	
Obsess-O-Matic 1.0 by Wayne Phillips  December, 1989

        Special thanks to: Lindsay Markus, Dave Owens, and Fred Werrell
                           for their ideas and friendship.
                      
            Obsess-O-Matic is a real-time puzzle game. The object
    is to fit the falling pieces together to form complete horizontal
    rows, which will then disappear off the bottom of the board. Once
    the pieces fill in and reach the top, the game is over.
            This Game is ShareWare...Please feel free to copy and give it
    to a friend or put it on any bulletin board. If you enjoy it, I would
    appreciate a donation very much. My address is:
                      
                    Wayne Phillips
                    1364 HiView Drive
                    Southampton, Pa. 18966
                      
            For a $10 donation, I will send you version 2.0 which
    will include: 
  
               1) Controllable board width & height (smaller board provides
                  a greater challenge and earns extra bonus points)
               2) Programmable starting height of blocks. (fills in random
                  blocks to a given height. Provides a challenge and earns
                  bonus points)
               3) The Pile Driver Piece
               4) Magnetic Walls
               5) Vaccine Piece
               6) Virus Piece
                      
            For $15 dollars or more, I will send you version 3.0 which
   will, in addition to the above, include:

               1) Animated sprite special effects.
               2) Graphic Puzzle Piece Editor to design your own 
                  puzzle piece sets.
               3) Several piece sets to try.

